cs.SC, cs.DS, cs.CC, cs.NA, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
- cs.SC (Symbolic Computation) is the most likely category as the paper discusses the implementation of a library for computing factors of polynomials, which falls under the domain of symbolic computation.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper discusses the complexity of the algorithms used in the implementation.
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is another possible category as the paper discusses the polynomial complexity of the algorithms used.
- cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) is a less likely category as the paper does not focus on numerical methods, but rather on symbolic computation.
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is also a less likely category as the paper does not discuss control systems, but rather focuses on the implementation of a library for polynomial factorization.
